column78: How to dress a sideboard? Add a statement piece, a lamp, or a decorative mirror positioned off-centre to create a visual focus rather than symmetry. Varying heights add to the aesthetics through stacked books, ceramic vessels, or botanical arrangements. A carefully curated selection of three to five objects prevents overcrowding whilst establishing presence. Try the rule of triangulation by adding items in odd-numbered groups, creating natural sightlines across the surface. Maintain adequate space between objects to allow each piece to command attention independently whilst contributing to the overall composition.
